This paper deals with fair division of indivisible goods, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper proposes a new algorithm that achieves good approximation guarantees for multiple fairness notions, which involves designing and analyzing algorithms (cs.AI), as well as using techniques from optimization and game theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the existence of fair allocations, which is a topic in mathematical aspects of computer science (cs.MA). Finally, the paper uses empirical evaluations to support its claims, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
